The bug reporting system on darkwind is quite featured and unique.  This document
will attempt to show some of the commands associtated with the bug system.  When
a player submits a bug|typo|idea|emote, a message is transmitted to the balance 
line for assignement.  Currently, most assignements are executed by Zureal, or 
other IMP+.  

To see what bugs are currently not assigned to anyone type:

		listunassigned bug|typo|idea|emote|all

To see which bugs are assigned to you type:

		listassigned bug|typo|idea|emote|all

Before you can close a bug assigned to you, you must first respond to that sumission.
To respond, type:

		respond bug|typo|idea|emote <sub ##>

Once you have responded to the submission and it has been fixed|added|rejected|etc you
then close the submission by typing:

		closesub bug|typo|idea|emote <sub ##>

If you want to see some general statistics about the overall submission situation type:

		listtally bug|typo|idea|emote|all
		listassignments bug|typo|idea|emote|all all|top open|closed|total <name>

To see what another wizard has assigned to them type:

		listassigned bug|typo|idea|emote|all <wizard name>

If you want to close a submission that was entered by error or any other reason that the
sumission should be closed without response, type:

		removesub bug|typo|idea|emote <sub ##>

To simply display the text of a bug type:

		lst bug|typo|idea|emote <sub ##>

To review all entries that are associated with a specific submission, type:

		listhistory bug|typo|idea|emote <sub ##>

If you are a member of the balance group to assign the initial sub or need to reassign
a submission to another wiz, use:

		assignsub bug|typo|idea|emote <sub ##> <wizard name>
		reassignsub bug|typo|idea|emote <sub ##> <wizard name>

If you need to edit a current submission type:

		editsub bug|typo|idea|emote (sub ##>



